hwWlanGlobalApUsername.name: hwWlanGlobalApUsername
hwWlanGlobalApUsername.description: This object indicates user names for Telnet-based login to APs.

hwWlanGlobalApPassword.description: This object indicates passwords for Telnet-based login to APs.

hwWlanGlobalIpv6Enable.description: This object indicates the status of the global IPv6 function. The default value is 1.

hwWlanStationIpv6Enable.description: This object indicates the status of the IPv6 function of users. The default value is 1 . 1: disable 2: enable.

hwWlanApDataCollectionInterval.description: This object indicates the period of caching AP performance. The default value is 15. It is expressed in minutes.

hwTestRtCollectOnoff.name: hwTestRtCollectOnoff
hwTestRtCollectOnoff.description: This object indicates the status of the real-time collection switch.

hwTestApNormalCollectCycle.name: hwTestApNormalCollectCycle
hwTestApNormalCollectCycle.description: This object indicates the regular period of an AC collecting AP performance data.

hwTestApRtCollectCycle.name: hwTestApRtCollectCycle
hwTestApRtCollectCycle.description: This object indicates the real-time period of an AC collecting AP performance data.

hwWlanProtectIpAddress.name: hwWlanProtectIpAddress
hwWlanProtectIpAddress.description: This object indicates the IP address of the standby AC.

hwWlanProtectIPv6Address.name: hwWlanProtectIPv6Address
hwWlanProtectIPv6Address.description: This object indicates setting of the IPv6 address of the standby AC.

hwWlanProtectPriority.name: hwWlanProtectPriority
hwWlanProtectPriority.description: This object indicates the AC priority that determines whether the AC can be selected as the active AC. The default value is 0.

hwWlanProtectSwitch.name: hwWlanProtectSwitch
hwWlanProtectSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the hot backup function. The default value is 2.

hwWlanProtectRestoreSwitch.name: hwWlanProtectRestoreSwitch
hwWlanProtectRestoreSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the switchback function. The default value is 1.

hwUndoWlanProtectIpAddress.name: hwUndoWlanProtectIpAddress
hwUndoWlanProtectIpAddress.description: This object indicates whether to restore the default setting of the IP address of the standby AC.

hwUndoWlanProtectPriority.name: hwUndoWlanProtectPriority
hwUndoWlanProtectPriority.description: This object indicates whether to restore the default setting of the priority of the standby AC.

hwWlanCfgHsbServiceType.description: This object indicates the HSB type. The default value is 1.

hwWlanCfgHsbGroupId.name: hwWlanCfgHsbGroupId
hwWlanCfgHsbGroupId.description: This object indicates the HSB group ID. If the HSB type is set to Disable, the ID is 0xFFFFFFFF.

hwWlanCfgHsbTunnelId.name: hwWlanCfgHsbTunnelId
hwWlanCfgHsbTunnelId.description: This object indicates the ID of the HSB channel. If the HSB type is set to Disable, the ID is 0xFFFFFFFF.

hwWlanReportStaInfo.name: hwWlanReportStaInfo
hwWlanReportStaInfo.description: This object indicates the switch of recording user information in the log. 1:disable 2:enable.

hwAPGroupName.description: This object indicates the AP group name. It is the index of the table.

hwAPGrpDomainProfile.description: This object indicates the domain profile to which AP groups are bound. The default value is default.

hwAPGrpRadio2gProfile.description: This object indicates the 2G radio profile to which AP groups are bound. The default value is default.

hwAPGrpRadioChannel.description: This object indicates a radio-frequency channel. For 2.4G, the value ranges from 1 to 13. For 5G, the value ranges from 36 to 196 (with a separation interval of 4).

hwAPGrpRadioBandwidth.name: hwAPGrpRadioBandwidth
hwAPGrpRadioBandwidth.description: This object indicate a bandwidth. The default value is 1.

hwAPGrpRadioEirp.name: hwAPGrpRadioEirp
hwAPGrpRadioEirp.description: This object indicates a power value. The default value is 127. The configuration is saved but the actual power is determined by the maximum power supported by the AP.

hwAPGrpRadioAntennaGain.description: This object indicates antenna gains. The default value 0xFF indicates that the default gain of an AP is used. It is expressed in dB. Default gains vary with different types of APs.

hwAPGrpRadioCoverageDistance.name: hwAPGrpRadioCoverageDistance
hwAPGrpRadioCoverageDistance.description: This object indicates a radio coverage distance. The default value is 3. The unit is 0.1 km.

hwAPGrpRadioWorkMode.name: hwAPGrpRadioWorkMode
hwAPGrpRadioWorkMode.description: This object indicates the radio working mode. The default value is 1.

hwAPGrpRadioFrequency.name: hwAPGrpRadioFrequency

hwAPGrpSpectrumAnalysisSwitch.name: hwAPGrpSpectrumAnalysisSwitch

hwAPGrpWidsDeviceDetectSwitch.name: hwAPGrpWidsDeviceDetectSwitch

hwAPGrpWidsRogueContainSwitch.name: hwAPGrpWidsRogueContainSwitch
hwAPGrpWidsRogueContainSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the device detection function. The default value is 1.

hwAPGrpRadioSecondChannel.name: hwAPGrpRadioSecondChannel
hwAPGrpRadioSecondChannel.description: This object indicates a radio-frequency channel. For 2.4G, the value ranges from 1 to 13. For 5G, the value ranges from 36 to 165 (with a separation interval of 4).

hwAPSpApIPv6PrefixLen.description: This object indicates the length of the IPv6 address prefix.

hwAPSpApIPv6Gateway.description: This object indicates the AP's IPv6 gateway. hwAPSpApIPv6Gateway takes effect if hwAPSpApAddressMode is set to static.

hwAPSpIPv4ACList.name: hwAPSpIPv4ACList
hwAPSpIPv4ACList.description: This object indicates the AC IPv4 address list. NOTE AC lists are separated by question marks (?).A maximum of four AC lists can be configured.

hwAPSpIPv6ACList.name: hwAPSpIPv6ACList
hwAPSpIPv6ACList.description: This object indicates the AC IPv6 address list. NOTE AC lists are separated by question marks (?).A maximum of four AC lists can be configured.

hwAPSpecificWiredPortTable.name: hwAPSpecificWiredPortTable
hwAPSpecificWiredPortTable.description: This table is used to bind an AP wired port profile to an AP specific profile or unbind an AP wired port profile from an AP specific profile..

hwAPSpecificWiredPortEntry.name: hwAPSpecificWiredPortEntry
hwAPSpecificWiredPortEntry.description: Indexes of this table are hwAPSpWPInterfaceType, hwAPSpWPInterfaceNum and hwAPSpApMac.

hwAPSpWPInterfaceType.name: hwAPSpWPInterfaceType
hwAPSpWPInterfaceType.description: This object indicates the interface type.

hwAPSpWPInterfaceNum.name: hwAPSpWPInterfaceNum
hwAPSpWPInterfaceNum.description: This object indicates the interface index.

hwAPSpWPProfile.name: hwAPSpWPProfile
hwAPSpWPProfile.description: This object indicates the bound wired port profile.

hwAPSpWPRowStatus.name: hwAPSpWPRowStatus
hwAPSpWPRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used? ROWSTATUS_UNDEFINED: undefined ? ROWSTATUS_DESTROY: destroy.

hwAPSpWPApId.name: hwAPSpWPApId
hwAPSpWPApId.description: This object indicates the AP ID.

hwAPSpecificRadioTable.name: hwAPSpecificRadioTable
hwAPSpecificRadioTable.description: This table records the information about profiles bound based on radio in an AP specific profile, including 5G radio profile, Mesh profile, WDS profile, WIDS profile, location profile, and spectrum profile.

hwAPSpecificRadioEntry.name: hwAPSpecificRadioEntry
hwAPSpecificRadioEntry.description: Indexes of this table are hwAPSpecificName and hwAPSpRadio.

hwAPSpRadio.name: hwAPSpRadio
hwAPSpRadio.description: This object indicates the radio ID. It is the index of the table.

hwAPSp5gRadioProfile.name: hwAPSp5gRadioProfile
hwAPSp5gRadioProfile.description: This object indicates the bound 5G radio profile.

hwAPSpMeshProfile.name: hwAPSpMeshProfile
hwAPSpMeshProfile.description: This object indicates the bound Mesh profile.

hwAPSpWdsProfile.name: hwAPSpWdsProfile
hwAPSpWdsProfile.description: This object indicates the bound WDS profile.

hwAPSpLocationProfile.name: hwAPSpLocationProfile
hwAPSpLocationProfile.description: This object indicates the bound location profile.

hwAPSpRadioRowStatus.name: hwAPSpRadioRowStatus
hwAPSpRadioRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwAPSpRadio2gProfile.name: hwAPSpRadio2gProfile
hwAPSpRadio2gProfile.description: This object indicates the system profile to which AP groups are bound. The default value is default.

hwAPSpMeshWhitelistProfile.name: hwAPSpMeshWhitelistProfile
hwAPSpMeshWhitelistProfile.description: This object indicates the bound whitelist profile.

hwAPSpWdsWhitelistProfile.name: hwAPSpWdsWhitelistProfile
hwAPSpWdsWhitelistProfile.description: This object indicates the bound whitelist profile.

hwAPSpRadioSwitch.name: hwAPSpRadioSwitch
hwAPSpRadioSwitch.description: This object indicates the name of a 2G radio profile. It is the index of the table.

hwAPSpRadioChannel.name: hwAPSpRadioChannel
hwAPSpRadioChannel.description: This object indicates a radio-frequency channel. For 2.4G, the value ranges from 1 to 13. For 5G, the value ranges from 36 to 196 (with a separation interval of 4).

hwAPSpRadioBandwidth.name: hwAPSpRadioBandwidth
hwAPSpRadioBandwidth.description: This object indicate a bandwidth. The default value is 1.

hwAPSpRadioEirp.name: hwAPSpRadioEirp
hwAPSpRadioEirp.description: This object indicates a power value. The default value is 127. The configuration is saved but the actual power is determined by the maximum power supported by the AP.

hwAPSpRadioAntennaGain.name: hwAPSpRadioAntennaGain
hwAPSpRadioAntennaGain.description: This object indicates antenna gains. The default value 0xFF indicates that the default gain of an AP is used. It is expressed in dB. Default gains vary with different types of APs.

hwAPSpRadioCoverageDistance.name: hwAPSpRadioCoverageDistance
hwAPSpRadioCoverageDistance.description: This object indicates a radio coverage distance. The default value is 3. The unit is 0.1 km.

hwAPSpRadioWorkMode.name: hwAPSpRadioWorkMode
hwAPSpRadioWorkMode.description: This object indicates the radio working mode. The default value is 1.

hwAPSpRadioFrequency.name: hwAPSpRadioFrequency
hwAPSpRadioFrequency.description: This object indicates the setting of the frequency band for radio 0. The default value is invalid. 1: frequency2G, 2: frequency5G.

hwAPSpSpectrumAnalysisSwitch.name: hwAPSpSpectrumAnalysisSwitch
hwAPSpSpectrumAnalysisSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the spectrum analysis function. The default value is 1.

hwAPSpWidsDeviceDetectSwitch.name: hwAPSpWidsDeviceDetectSwitch
hwAPSpWidsDeviceDetectSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the device detection function. The default value is 1.

hwAPSpWidsAttackDetectEnBmp.name: hwAPSpWidsAttackDetectEnBmp
hwAPSpWidsAttackDetectEnBmp.description: This object indicates the bit map of the brute force attack switch. bit0:weak-iv, bit1:spoof, bit2:flood, bit3:wpa-psk, bit4:wpa2-psk, bit5:wapi-psk, bit6:wep-psk.

hwAPSpWidsRogueContainSwitch.name: hwAPSpWidsRogueContainSwitch
hwAPSpWidsRogueContainSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the device detection function. The default value is 1.

hwAPSpRadioApId.name: hwAPSpRadioApId
hwAPSpRadioApId.description: This object indicates the AP ID.

hwAPSpRadioSecondChannel.name: hwAPSpRadioSecondChannel
hwAPSpRadioSecondChannel.description: This object indicates a radio-frequency channel. For 2.4G, the value ranges from 1 to 13. For 5G, the value ranges from 36 to 165 (with a separation interval of 4).

hwAPSpecificVapTable.name: hwAPSpecificVapTable
hwAPSpecificVapTable.description: This table is used to create VAPs in an AP specific profile.

hwAPSpecificVapEntry.name: hwAPSpecificVapEntry
hwAPSpecificVapEntry.description: Indexes of this table are hwAPSpWlan, hwAPSpRadio, and hwAPSpApMac.

hwAPSpWlan.name: hwAPSpWlan
hwAPSpWlan.description: This object indicates the WLAN ID. It is the index of the table.

hwAPSpVapProfile.name: hwAPSpVapProfile
hwAPSpVapProfile.description: This object indicates the bound VAP profile.

hwAPSpVapRowStatus.name: hwAPSpVapRowStatus
hwAPSpVapRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. createAndGo(4) and destroy(6) are commonly used.

hwAPSpVapApId.name: hwAPSpVapApId
hwAPSpVapApId.description: This object indicates the AP ID.

hwRegulatoryDomainProfileTable.name: hwRegulatoryDomainProfileTable
hwRegulatoryDomainProfileTable.description: This table is used to configure country codes, calibration channels, and calibration channel bandwidths.

hwRegulatoryDomainProfileEntry.name: hwRegulatoryDomainProfileEntry
hwRegulatoryDomainProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwRegulatoryDomainProfileName.

hwRegulatoryDomainProfileName.name: hwRegulatoryDomainProfileName
hwRegulatoryDomainProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of a regulatory domain profile. It is the index of the table.

hwCountryCode.name: hwCountryCode
hwCountryCode.description: This object indicates the country code. Its value range is subject to the country code table. The default value is CN.

hwDcaChannel5GBandwidth.name: hwDcaChannel5GBandwidth
hwDcaChannel5GBandwidth.description: This object indicates the calibration bandwidth on the 5 GHz frequency band. The default value is 1 ? 1: bw20 MHz ? 2: bw40 MHz ? 3: bw80 MHz.

hwDcaChannel5GChannelSet.name: hwDcaChannel5GChannelSet
hwDcaChannel5GChannelSet.description: This object indicates the calibration channel set on the 5 GHz frequency band.

hwDcaChannel2GChannelSet.name: hwDcaChannel2GChannelSet
hwDcaChannel2GChannelSet.description: This object indicates the calibration channel set on the 2 GHz frequency band.

hwRegulatoryDomainProfilRowStatus.name: hwRegulatoryDomainProfilRowStatus
hwRegulatoryDomainProfilRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used ? ROWSTATUS_UNDEFINED: undefined ? ROWSTATUS_ACTIVE: active ? ROWSTATUS_NOTINSERVICE: notInService ? ROWSTATUS_NOTREADY: notReady ? ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW: createAndGo ? ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDWAIT: createAndWait ? ROWSTATUS_DESTROY: destroy.

hwWlanWideBandEnable.name: hwWlanWideBandEnable
hwWlanWideBandEnable.description: This object indicates wide band status. The default value is disable.

hwApSystemProfileTable.name: hwApSystemProfileTable
hwApSystemProfileTable.description: This table is used to create or delete an AP system profile and configure AP attributes.

hwApSystemProfileEntry.name: hwApSystemProfileEntry
hwApSystemProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwApSystemProfName.

hwApSystemProfName.name: hwApSystemProfName
hwApSystemProfName.description: This object indicates the name of an AP system profile. It is the index of the table.

hwApProfSampleTime.name: hwApProfSampleTime
hwApProfSampleTime.description: This object indicates the sampling interval for the AC to collecting AP performance data. The default value is 30. It is expressed in seconds.

hwApProfLedSwitch.name: hwApProfLedSwitch
hwApProfLedSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to enable the AP's LED indicator. The default value is 2.

hwApProfMaxStaNum.name: hwApProfMaxStaNum
hwApProfMaxStaNum.description: This object indicates the maximum number of access users on an AP. The default value is 128.

hwApProfMtu.name: hwApProfMtu
hwApProfMtu.description: This object indicates the MTU of an AP interface. The default value is 1500.

hwApProfMeshRole.name: hwApProfMeshRole
hwApProfMeshRole.description: This object indicates a Mesh role. The default value is 1.

hwApProfTemporaryManagement.name: hwApProfTemporaryManagement
hwApProfTemporaryManagement.description: This object indicates the status of the AP-based offline VAP switch. The default value is 1.

hwApProfManagementVlan.name: hwApProfManagementVlan
hwApProfManagementVlan.description: This object indicates the management VLAN for APs. The default value is 1.

hwApProfHighTempThreshold.name: hwApProfHighTempThreshold
hwApProfHighTempThreshold.description: This object indicates the high temperature alarm threshold on an AP. The default value 0xFFFFFFFF indicates the system threshold of the AP NOTE System thresholds vary with different AP types. For details, see AP device information.

hwApProfLowTempThreshold.name: hwApProfLowTempThreshold
hwApProfLowTempThreshold.description: This object indicates the low temperature alarm threshold on an AP. The default value 0xFFFF indicates the system threshold of the AP.

hwApProfOpHRxPowerThreshold.name: hwApProfOpHRxPowerThreshold
hwApProfOpHRxPowerThreshold.description: This object indicates the high power threshold of an optical module. The default value is 1000.

hwApProfOpLRxPowerThreshold.name: hwApProfOpLRxPowerThreshold
hwApProfOpLRxPowerThreshold.description: This object indicates the low power threshold of an optical module. The default value is 50.

hwApProfOpHTempThreshold.name: hwApProfOpHTempThreshold
hwApProfOpHTempThreshold.description: This object indicates the high temperature threshold of an optical module. The default value is 70.

hwApProfOpLTempThreshold.name: hwApProfOpLTempThreshold
hwApProfOpLTempThreshold.description: This object indicates the low temperature threshold of an optical module. The default value is -5.

hwApProfMemoryUsageThreshold.name: hwApProfMemoryUsageThreshold
hwApProfMemoryUsageThreshold.description: This object indicates the memory usage alarm threshold of an AP. The default value is 80. It is expressed in percentage.

hwApProfCpuUsageThreshold.name: hwApProfCpuUsageThreshold
hwApProfCpuUsageThreshold.description: This object indicates the CPU usage alarm threshold of an AP. The default value is 90. It is expressed in percentage.

hwApProfTelnetSwitch.name: hwApProfTelnetSwitch
hwApProfTelnetSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to enable Telnet. The default value is 1.

hwApProfSTelnetSwitch.name: hwApProfSTelnetSwitch
hwApProfSTelnetSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to enable SSH. The default value is 2.

hwApProfConsoleSwitch.name: hwApProfConsoleSwitch
hwApProfConsoleSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to enable the console. The default value is 2.

hwApProfLogRecordLevel.name: hwApProfLogRecordLevel
hwApProfLogRecordLevel.description: This object indicates the log backup level. The default value is 7.

hwApProfLogServerIp.name: hwApProfLogServerIp
hwApProfLogServerIp.description: This object indicates the IP address of the log server.

hwApProfLogServerIpv6.name: hwApProfLogServerIpv6
hwApProfLogServerIpv6.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address of the log server.

hwApProfAlarmRestrictionSwitch.name: hwApProfAlarmRestrictionSwitch
hwApProfAlarmRestrictionSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the alarm suppression switch. The default value is 2.

hwApProfAlarmRestrictionPeriod.name: hwApProfAlarmRestrictionPeriod
hwApProfAlarmRestrictionPeriod.description: This object indicates the alarm suppression period. The default value is 60 seconds.

hwApProfKeepServiceSwitch.name: hwApProfKeepServiceSwitch
hwApProfKeepServiceSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to enable the offline service retaining function. The default value is 2.

hwApProfProtectPriority.name: hwApProfProtectPriority
hwApProfProtectPriority.description: This object indicates the AC priority. A smaller value indicates a higher priority. The default value 0xFFFFFFFF indicates that no priority is configured.

hwApProfProtectACIp.name: hwApProfProtectACIp
hwApProfProtectACIp.description: This object indicates the IP address of the standby AC.

hwApProfProtectACIpv6.name: hwApProfProtectACIpv6
hwApProfProtectACIpv6.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address of the standby AC.

hwApProfEapStartMode.name: hwApProfEapStartMode
hwApProfEapStartMode.description: This object indicates the EAP Start packet conversion mode. The default value is 2.

hwApProfEapStartTransform.name: hwApProfEapStartTransform
hwApProfEapStartTransform.description: This object indicates the EAP Start packet conversion mode. The default value is 2.

hwApProfEapStartUnicastMac.name: hwApProfEapStartUnicastMac
hwApProfEapStartUnicastMac.description: This object indicates that EAP Start packets are converted to those with specific MAC addresses.

hwApProfEapResponseMode.name: hwApProfEapResponseMode
hwApProfEapResponseMode.description: This object indicates the EAP Response packet conversion mode. The default value is 2.

hwApProfEapResponseTransform.name: hwApProfEapResponseTransform
hwApProfEapResponseTransform.description: This object indicates the EAP Response packet conversion mode. The default value is 4.

hwApProfEapResponseUnicastMac.name: hwApProfEapResponseUnicastMac
hwApProfEapResponseUnicastMac.description: This object indicates that EAP Response packets are converted to those with specific MAC addresses.

hwApProfLldpRestartDelay.name: hwApProfLldpRestartDelay
hwApProfLldpRestartDelay.description: This object indicates the delay for re-enabling LLDP. The default value is 2. It is expressed in seconds.

hwApProfLldpAdminStatus.name: hwApProfLldpAdminStatus
hwApProfLldpAdminStatus.description: This object indicates the operation mode of LLDP. The default value is 1.

hwApProfLldpRetransDelay.name: hwApProfLldpRetransDelay
hwApProfLldpRetransDelay.description: This object indicates the message retransmitting delay. The default value is 2. It is expressed in seconds.

hwApProfLldpRetransHoldMultiplier.name: hwApProfLldpRetransHoldMultiplier
hwApProfLldpRetransHoldMultiplier.description: This object indicates the hold time multiplier of device information on neighbors (cardinal number is the interval time). The default value is 4.

hwApProfLldpInterval.name: hwApProfLldpInterval
hwApProfLldpInterval.description: This object indicates the interval at which LLDP packets are sent. The default value is 30 seconds.

hwApProfLldpReportInterval.name: hwApProfLldpReportInterval
hwApProfLldpReportInterval.description: This object indicates the interval at which LLDP packets are reported. The default value is 30 seconds.

hwApProfStaAccessMode.name: hwApProfStaAccessMode
hwApProfStaAccessMode.description: This object indicates the access mode. The default value is 1.

hwApProfStaAccessModeProfile.name: hwApProfStaAccessModeProfile
hwApProfStaAccessModeProfile.description: This object indicates blacklist and whitelist profiles.

hwApProfRowStatus.name: hwApProfRowStatus
hwApProfRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used ? ROWSTATUS_UNDEFINED: undefined ? ROWSTATUS_ACTIVE: active ? ROWSTATUS_NOTINSERVICE: notInService ? ROWSTATUS_NOTREADY: notReady ? ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW: createAndGo ? ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDWAIT: createAndWait ? ROWSTATUS_DESTROY: destroy.

hwApProfSFTPSwitch.name: hwApProfSFTPSwitch
hwApProfSFTPSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to enable the SFTP. The default value is 2.

hwApProfDynamicBlackListAgingTime.name: hwApProfDynamicBlackListAgingTime
hwApProfDynamicBlackListAgingTime.description: This object indicates the aging time of the dynamic blacklist entries. The default value is 600.

hwApProfMppActiveReselectionSwitch.name: hwApProfMppActiveReselectionSwitch
hwApProfMppActiveReselectionSwitch.description: This object indicates of mpp active reselection.

hwApProfSpectrumServerIPAddress.name: hwApProfSpectrumServerIPAddress
hwApProfSpectrumServerIPAddress.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address of the spectrum analysis server. You choose an IPv4 or IPv6 address. By default, the IPv4 address 255.255.255.255 is used.

hwApProfSpectrumServerIPv6Address.name: hwApProfSpectrumServerIPv6Address
hwApProfSpectrumServerIPv6Address.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address of the spectrum analysis server. You choose an IPv4 or IPv6 address. By default, it is not configured.

hwApProfSpectrumServerPort.name: hwApProfSpectrumServerPort
hwApProfSpectrumServerPort.description: This object indicates the port of the spectrum analysis server. The default value is 32181.

hwApProfSpectrumViaACSwitch.name: hwApProfSpectrumViaACSwitch
hwApProfSpectrumViaACSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the spectrum analysis function. The default value is 2.

hwApProfSpectrumViaACPort.name: hwApProfSpectrumViaACPort
hwApProfSpectrumViaACPort.description: This object indicates the port number used by the AP to report spectrum analysis data to the AC. The default value is 6412.

hwApProfSpectrumNonWifiDeviceAgingTime.name: hwApProfSpectrumNonWifiDeviceAgingTime
hwApProfSpectrumNonWifiDeviceAgingTime.description: This object indicates the aging time of non-WLAN devices on the AC. The default value is 3 minutes.

hwApProfPoeMaxPower.name: hwApProfPoeMaxPower
hwApProfPoeMaxPower.description: This object indicates the maximum output power of the AP.The default value is 380000.

hwApProfPoePowerReserved.name: hwApProfPoePowerReserved
hwApProfPoePowerReserved.description: This object indicates the percentage of reserved PoE power to the available PoE power.The default value is 0.

hwApProfPoePowerThreshold.name: hwApProfPoePowerThreshold
hwApProfPoePowerThreshold.description: This object indicates the alarm threshold of PoE power consumption percentage.The default value is 100.

hwApProfPoeAfInrushSwitch.name: hwApProfPoeAfInrushSwitch
hwApProfPoeAfInrushSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to enable the IEEE 802.3at-compliant device to provide power in accordance with IEEE 802.3af.The default value is 1.

hwApProfPoeHighInrushSwitch.name: hwApProfPoeHighInrushSwitch
hwApProfPoeHighInrushSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to enable the device to allow high inrush current during power-on.The default value is 1.

hwApProfPrimaryLinkIPv4.name: hwApProfPrimaryLinkIPv4
hwApProfPrimaryLinkIPv4.description: This object indicates the IP address of the primary AC.

hwApProfPrimaryLinkIPv6.name: hwApProfPrimaryLinkIPv6
hwApProfPrimaryLinkIPv6.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address of the primary AC.

hwApProfBackupLinkIPv4.name: hwApProfBackupLinkIPv4
hwApProfBackupLinkIPv4.description: This object indicates the IP address of the backup AC.

hwApProfBackupLinkIPv6.name: hwApProfBackupLinkIPv6
hwApProfBackupLinkIPv6.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address of the backup AC.

hwApProfLedOffTimeRange.name: hwApProfLedOffTimeRange
hwApProfLedOffTimeRange.description: This object indicates whether to make a configured Led off time range effective.

hwApProfUsbSwitch.name: hwApProfUsbSwitch
hwApProfUsbSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to enable the USB. The default value is 1.

hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionArpEnable.name: hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionArpEnable
hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionArpEnable.description: This object indicates whether to enable the arp broadcast suppression.The default value is 1.

hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionArpThreshold.name: hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionArpThreshold
hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionArpThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold of arp broadcast suppression. The default value is 256.

hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionIgmpEnable.name: hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionIgmpEnable
hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionIgmpEnable.description: This object indicates whether to enable the igmp broadcast suppression.The default value is 1.

hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionIgmpThreshol.name: hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionIgmpThreshold
hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionIgmpThreshol.description: This object indicates the threshold of igmp broadcast suppression. The default value is 256.

hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionNdEnable.name: hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionNdEnable
hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionNdEnable.description: This object indicates whether to enable the nd broadcast suppression.The default value is 1.

hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionNdThreshold.name: hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionNdThreshold
hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionNdThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold of nd broadcast suppression. The default value is 256.

hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionOtherEnable.name: hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionOtherEnable
hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionOtherEnable.description: This object indicates whether to enable the other broadcast suppression.The default value is 1.

hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionOtherThresho.name: hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionOtherThreshold
hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionOtherThresho.description: This object indicates the threshold of other broadcast suppression. The default value is 256.

hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionAllEnable.name: hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionAllEnable
hwApProfBroadcastSuppressionAllEnable.description: This object indicates whether to enable all the broadcast suppression.The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfileTable.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileTable
hwAPWiredPortProfileTable.description: This table is used to create or delete an AP wired port link profile and modify or query attributes.

hwAPWiredPortProfileEntry.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileEntry
hwAPWiredPortProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwAPWiredPortProfileName.

hwAPWiredPortProfileName.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileName
hwAPWiredPortProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of an AP wired port link profile.

hwAPWiredPortPortLinkProfileName.name: hwAPWiredPortPortLinkProfileName
hwAPWiredPortPortLinkProfileName.description: This object indicates the bound AP wired port link profile.

hwAPWiredPortProfilePortDesc.name: hwAPWiredPortProfilePortDesc
hwAPWiredPortProfilePortDesc.description: This object indicates the description of an interface.

hwAPWiredPortProfilePortEthTrunkID.name: hwAPWiredPortProfilePortEthTrunkID
hwAPWiredPortProfilePortEthTrunkID.description: This object indicates the ID of a Trunk. 0 is valid and 0xFFFFFFFF is invalid. The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF.

hwAPWiredPortProfilePortSTPSwitch.name: hwAPWiredPortProfilePortSTPSwitch
hwAPWiredPortProfilePortSTPSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to enable STP on wired ports. The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfilePortMode.name: hwAPWiredPortProfilePortMode
hwAPWiredPortProfilePortMode.description: This object indicates the mode of the wired port. For FE ports of plate APs, the default value is 2. For other ports, the default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfilePortVlanPvid.name: hwAPWiredPortProfilePortVlanPvid
hwAPWiredPortProfilePortVlanPvid.description: This object indicates the PVID of a port. The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfilePortVlanTagged.name: hwAPWiredPortProfilePortVlanTagged
hwAPWiredPortProfilePortVlanTagged.description: This object indicates whether to tag ports with VLAN IDs. The default value is 0.

hwAPWiredPortProfilePortVlanUntagged.name: hwAPWiredPortProfilePortVlanUntagged
hwAPWiredPortProfilePortVlanUntagged.description: This object indicates whether to untag VLAN IDS from ports. The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfileUserIsolate.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileUserIsolate
hwAPWiredPortProfileUserIsolate.description: This object indicates the status of the user isolation function. The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfileDhcpTrust.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileDhcpTrust
hwAPWiredPortProfileDhcpTrust.description: This object indicates whether a port is configured as a DHCP trusted port. The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfileNdTrust.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileNdTrust
hwAPWiredPortProfileNdTrust.description: This object indicates whether a port is configured as a ND trusted port. The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfileRowStatus.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileRowStatus
hwAPWiredPortProfileRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwAPWiredPortProfileLearnAddress.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileLearnAddress
hwAPWiredPortProfileLearnAddress.description: This object indicates whether to enable address learning.The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfileIpBindCheck.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileIpBindCheck
hwAPWiredPortProfileIpBindCheck.description: This object indicates whether to enable IP packet checking against the binding table.The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfileArpBindCheck.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileArpBindCheck
hwAPWiredPortProfileArpBindCheck.description: This object indicates whether to enable ARP packet checking against the binding table.The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfileSTPAutoShutdown.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileSTPAutoShutdown
hwAPWiredPortProfileSTPAutoShutdown.description: This object indicates whether to enable STP-triggered port shutdown.The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfileSTPAutoShutdownRecov.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileSTPAutoShutdownRecoveryTime
hwAPWiredPortProfileSTPAutoShutdownRecov.description: This object indicates the automatic port recovery time after an STP-triggered shutdown.The default value is 600.

hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficOptimizeSuppr.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficOptimizeSuppressionBc
hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficOptimizeSuppr.description: This object indicates the rate limit for broadcast storm suppression.The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF.

hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficOptimizeSuppr.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficOptimizeSuppressionUc
hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficOptimizeSuppr.description: This object indicates the rate limit for unknown unicast storm suppression.The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF.

hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficOptimizeSuppr.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficOptimizeSuppressionMc
hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficOptimizeSuppr.description: This object indicates the rate limit for multicast storm suppression.The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF.

hwAPWiredPortProfileIGMPSnooping.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileIGMPSnooping
hwAPWiredPortProfileIGMPSnooping.description: This object indicates whether to enable IGMP-snooping.The default value is 1.

hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficFilterTable.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficFilterTable
hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficFilterTable.description: This table is used to configure ACL-based packet filtering in an AP wired port profile.

hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficFilterEntry.name: hwAPWiredPortProfileTrafficFilterEntry

hw5gRadioApEDCABKECWmax.name: hw5gRadioApEDCABKECWmax
hw5gRadioApEDCABKECWmax.description: This object indicates the EDCA parameter ECWmax, namely, exponent form of Cwmax, for BK services on APs. ECWmin and ECWmax determine the average backoff time (ECWmax > ECWmin). The default value is 10.

hw5gRadioApEDCABKECWmin.name: hw5gRadioApEDCABKECWmin
hw5gRadioApEDCABKECWmin.description: This object indicates the EDCA parameter ECWmin, namely, exponent form of Cwmin, for BK services on APs. ECWmin and ECWmax determine the average backoff time (ECWmax > ECWmin). The default value is 4.

hw5gRadioApEDCABKAIFSN.name: hw5gRadioApEDCABKAIFSN
hw5gRadioApEDCABKAIFSN.description: This object indicates the EDCA parameter AIFSN, namely, arbitration interframe spacing number, for BK services on APs. The default value is 7..

hw5gRadioApEDCABKTXOPLimit.name: hw5gRadioApEDCABKTXOPLimit
hw5gRadioApEDCABKTXOPLimit.description: This object indicates the EDCA parameter TXOPLimit, namely, transmission opportunity limit, for BK services on APs. The default value is 0. The unit is 32 us.

hw5gRadioApEDCABKAckPolicy.name: hw5gRadioApEDCABKAckPolicy
hw5gRadioApEDCABKAckPolicy.description: This object indicates the EDCA parameter AckPolicy for BK services on APs. The default value is 1.

hw5gRadioWmmSwitch.name: hw5gRadioWmmSwitch
hw5gRadioWmmSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the WMM function. The default value is 2.

hw5gRadioRtsCtsThreshold.name: hw5gRadioRtsCtsThreshold
hw5gRadioRtsCtsThreshold.description: This object indicates the request To Send/Clear To Send (RTS/CTS) threshold. If the length of a frame to be sent by the MAC Layer exceeds this threshold, an RTS frame needs to be sent before this frame. The default value is 2347 bytes.

hw5gRadioRtsCtsMode.name: hw5gRadioRtsCtsMode
hw5gRadioRtsCtsMode.description: This object indicates the RTS-CTS mode set for the specified radio profile. The default value is 2.

hw5gRadioPowerAutoAdjustSwitch.name: hw5gRadioPowerAutoAdjustSwitch
hw5gRadioPowerAutoAdjustSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the user-by-user power control function. The default value is 1.

hw5gRadioBeamformingSwitch.name: hw5gRadioBeamformingSwitch
hw5gRadioBeamformingSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the beamforming function. The default value is 1.

hw5gRadioWifiLight.name: hw5gRadioWifiLight
hw5gRadioWifiLight.description: This object indicates information reflected by the blinking frequency of the Wireless LED on an AP. The default value is 1 NOTE ? If Mesh is enabled on an AP, the Wireless indicator blinking frequency reflects the signal strength of the AP with the weakest signal among received signals from all neighboring APs.? If WDS is enabled on an AP, the the Wireless indicator blinking frequency reflects the signal strength of the connected WDS AP.? For a Leaf AP, the Wireless indicator blinking frequency reflects the signal strength of the connected Middle AP.? For a Middle AP, the Wireless indicator blinking frequency reflects the signal strength of the connected Root AP.? For a root AP, the Wireless indicator blinking frequency reflects the signal strength of the connected Middle AP with the weakest signal.? If WDS or Mesh is not enabled on an AP, the Wireless indicator blinking frequency reflects the service traffic volume on the radio.

hw5gRadioChannelSwitchAnnouncementSwitch.name: hw5gRadioChannelSwitchAnnouncementSwitch
hw5gRadioChannelSwitchAnnouncementSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the channel switchover announcement function. The default value is 2.

hw5gRadioChannelSwitchMode.name: hw5gRadioChannelSwitchMode
hw5gRadioChannelSwitchMode.description: This object indicates the channel switch announcement mode. The default value is 1.

hw5gRadioAutoOffServiceSwitch.name: hw5gRadioAutoOffServiceSwitch
hw5gRadioAutoOffServiceSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the scheduled radio disabling function. The default value is 1.

hw5gRadioAutoOffServiceStartTime.name: hw5gRadioAutoOffServiceStartTime
hw5gRadioAutoOffServiceStartTime.description: This object indicates the start time for disabling the radio. The value is in the format of hh:mm:ss NOTE ? hh specifies the hour. The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 23.? mm specifies the minute. The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 59.? ss specifies the second. The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 59..

hw5gRadioAutoOffServiceEndTime.name: hw5gRadioAutoOffServiceEndTime
hw5gRadioAutoOffServiceEndTime.description: This object indicates the end time for disabling of the radio. The value is in the format of hh:mm:ss. NOTE? hh specifies the hour. The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 23.? mm specifies the minute. The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 59.? ss specifies the second. The value is an integer that ranges from 0 to 59.

hw5gRadioInterferenceDetectSwitch.name: hw5gRadioInterferenceDetectSwitch
hw5gRadioInterferenceDetectSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the user-by-user power control function. The default value is 1.

hw5gRadioInterferenceIntraFrequencyThres.name: hw5gRadioInterferenceIntraFrequencyThreshold
hw5gRadioInterferenceIntraFrequencyThres.description: This object indicates the alarm threshold for co-channel interference, namely, the percentage of the co-channel interference power against the maximum power. The default value is 50.

hw5gRadioInterferenceAdjacentFrequencyTh.name: hw5gRadioInterferenceAdjacentFrequencyThreshold
hw5gRadioInterferenceAdjacentFrequencyTh.description: This object indicates the alarm threshold for adjacent-channel interference, namely, the percentage of the adjacent-channel interference power against the maximum power. The default value is 50.

hw5gRadioInterferenceStationThreshold.name: hw5gRadioInterferenceStationThreshold
hw5gRadioInterferenceStationThreshold.description: This object indicates the alarm threshold for adjacent-channel interference. When the number of the STAs detected exceeds the specified alarm threshold, the AP reports alarms to the AC. The default value is 32.

hw5gRadioRrmProfile.name: hw5gRadioRrmProfile
hw5gRadioRrmProfile.description: This object indicates the bound RRM profile.

hw5gRadioAirScanProfile.name: hw5gRadioAirScanProfile
hw5gRadioAirScanProfile.description: This object indicates the bound air scan profile.

hw5gRadioProfileRowStatus.name: hw5gRadioProfileRowStatus
hw5gRadioProfileRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.? ROWSTATUS_UNDEFINED: undefined? ROWSTATUS_ACTIVE: active? ROWSTATUS_NOTINSERVICE: notInService? ROWSTATUS_NOTREADY: notReady? ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW: createAndGo? ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDWAIT: createAndWait? ROWSTATUS_DESTROY: destroy.

hw5gRadioProfileUtmostPowerSwitch.name: hw5gRadioProfileUtmostPowerSwitch
hw5gRadioProfileUtmostPowerSwitch.description: This object indicates the switch for the function of sending packets at maximum power.

hw5gRadioProfileRadioType.name: hw5gRadioProfileRadioType
hw5gRadioProfileRadioType.description: This object indicates the type of radio. The default value is 14.

hw5gRadioProfileAutoOffTimeRange.name: hw5gRadioProfileAutoOffTimeRange
hw5gRadioProfileAutoOffTimeRange.description: This object indicates the time range for disabling the radio.

hwRrmProfileTable.name: hwRrmProfileTable
hwRrmProfileTable.description: This table is used to configure radio resource management parameters, including parameters related to band steering, dynamic load balancing, smart roaming, and UAC.

hwRrmProfileEntry.name: hwRrmProfileEntry
hwRrmProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwRrmProfileName.

hwRrmProfileName.name: hwRrmProfileName
hwRrmProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of the RRM profile. It is the index of the table.

hwRrmAutoChannelSelectSwitch.name: hwRrmAutoChannelSelectSwitch
hwRrmAutoChannelSelectSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the automatic channel selection function. The default value is 2.

hwRrmAutoTxPowerSelectSwitch.name: hwRrmAutoTxPowerSelectSwitch
hwRrmAutoTxPowerSelectSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the automatic power selection function. The default value is 2.

hwRrmErrRateThreshold.name: hwRrmErrRateThreshold
hwRrmErrRateThreshold.description: This object indicate the error packet threshold triggering the automatic channel or power selection function. The default value is 50. It is expressed in percentage.

hwRrmAirtimeFairSchduleSwitch.name: hwRrmAirtimeFairSchduleSwitch
hwRrmAirtimeFairSchduleSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the airtime scheduling function. The default value is 1.

hwRrmDynamicEdcaSwitch.name: hwRrmDynamicEdcaSwitch
hwRrmDynamicEdcaSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the dynamic EDCA parameter adjustment function. The default value is 1.

hwRrmUacLimitClientSnrSwitch.name: hwRrmUacLimitClientSnrSwitch
hwRrmUacLimitClientSnrSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the rejecting access from terminals with weak signals function. The default value is 1.

hwRrmUacClientSnrThreshold.name: hwRrmUacClientSnrThreshold
hwRrmUacClientSnrThreshold.description: This object indicates the SNR threshold for rejecting access from terminals. The default value is 15. It is expressed in dB.

hwRrmUacPolicySwitch.name: hwRrmUacPolicySwitch
hwRrmUacPolicySwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the UAC policy function. The default value is 1.

hwRrmUacPolicyType.name: hwRrmUacPolicyType
hwRrmUacPolicyType.description: This object indicates the UAC policy. The default value is 1.

hwRrmUacReachThresholdHideSsidSwitch.name: hwRrmUacReachThresholdHideSsidSwitch
hwRrmUacReachThresholdHideSsidSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the function of hiding the SSID when the value of UAC reaches the specified threshold. The default value is 1.

hwRrmBandSteerDenyThreshold.name: hwRrmBandSteerDenyThreshold
hwRrmBandSteerDenyThreshold.description: This object indicates the maximum number of times the band steering function rejects association requests from terminals. The default value is 2.

hwRrmBandSteerLbClientThreshold.name: hwRrmBandSteerLbClientThreshold
hwRrmBandSteerLbClientThreshold.description: This object indicates the minimum number of terminals for triggering inter-band load balancing. The default value is 10..

hwRrmBandSteerClientBandsExpire.name: hwRrmBandSteerClientBandsExpire
hwRrmBandSteerClientBandsExpire.description: This object indicates the load difference percentage for triggering inter-band load balancing. The default value is 20.

hwRrmLoadBalanceSwitch.name: hwRrmLoadBalanceSwitch
hwRrmLoadBalanceSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the load balancing group function. The default value is 1.

hwRrmLoadBalanceClientThreshold.name: hwRrmLoadBalanceClientThreshold
hwRrmLoadBalanceClientThreshold.description: This object indicates the percentage of terminals for triggering load balancing. The default value is 10. It is expressed in percentage.

hwRrmLoadBalanceGapThreshold.name: hwRrmLoadBalanceGapThreshold
hwRrmLoadBalanceGapThreshold.description: This object indicates the load difference threshold for triggering load balancing, which is expressed in the number of terminals. The default value is 10.

hwRrmLoadBalanceDenyThreshold.name: hwRrmLoadBalanceDenyThreshold
hwRrmLoadBalanceDenyThreshold.description: This object indicates the maximum number of times the load balancing function rejects association requests from terminals. The default value is 3.

hwRrmSmartRoamCheckType.name: hwRrmSmartRoamCheckType
hwRrmSmartRoamCheckType.description: This object indicates whether STA active roaming is triggered by rate check or SNR check.The values are as follows:? 1: checkSnr? 2: checkRate? 3: checkAll.

hwRrmSmartRoamSwitch.name: hwRrmSmartRoamSwitch
hwRrmSmartRoamSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the smart roaming function. The default value is 1.

hwRrmSmartRoamSnrThreshold.name: hwRrmSmartRoamSnrThreshold
hwRrmSmartRoamSnrThreshold.description: This object indicates the SNR threshold for triggering the smart roaming function. The default value is 20 dB.

hwRrmSmartRoamRateThreshold.name: hwRrmSmartRoamRateThreshold
hwRrmSmartRoamRateThreshold.description: This object indicates the rate threshold for triggering the smart roaming function. It is expressed in the percentage against the maximum rate supported by the terminal. The default value is 0. It is expressed in percentage.

hwRrmSmartRoamSnrHighLevelMargin.name: hwRrmSmartRoamSnrHighLevelMargin
hwRrmSmartRoamSnrHighLevelMargin.description: This object indicates the upper SNR difference threshold for triggering smart roaming. The default value is 15. It is expressed in dB.

hwRrmSmartRoamSnrLowLevelMargin.name: hwRrmSmartRoamSnrLowLevelMargin
hwRrmSmartRoamSnrLowLevelMargin.description: This object indicates the lower SNR difference threshold for triggering smart roaming. The default value is 6. It is expressed in dB.

hwRrmSmartRoamSnrCheckInterval.name: hwRrmSmartRoamSnrCheckInterval
hwRrmSmartRoamSnrCheckInterval.description: This object indicates the terminal SNR detection interval for smart roaming. The default value is 3. It is expressed in s.

hwRrmSmartRoamUnableRoamExpireTime.name: hwRrmSmartRoamUnableRoamExpireTime
hwRrmSmartRoamUnableRoamExpireTime.description: This object indicates the aging time of records that terminals are unable to roam. The default value is 240. It is expressed in minutes.

hwRrmProfileRowStatus.name: hwRrmProfileRowStatus
hwRrmProfileRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwAirScanProfileTable.name: hwAirScanProfileTable
hwAirScanProfileTable.description: This table is used to configure air scan intervals, duration, and scan channel sets.

hwAirScanProfileEntry.name: hwAirScanProfileEntry
hwAirScanProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwAirScanProfileName.

hwAirScanProfileName.name: hwAirScanProfileName
hwAirScanProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of an air scan profile. It is the index of the table.

hwAirScanPeriod.name: hwAirScanPeriod
hwAirScanPeriod.description: This object indicates the air scan period. The default value is 60. It is expressed in ms.

hwAirScanInterval.name: hwAirScanInterval
hwAirScanInterval.description: This object indicates the scan interval. The default value is 600. The unit is 0.1s.

hwAirScanChannelSet.name: hwAirScanChannelSet
hwAirScanChannelSet.description: This object indicates the scan channel set. The default value is 1.

hwAirScanProfilRowStatus.name: hwAirScanProfilRowStatus
hwAirScanProfilRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.? ROWSTATUS_UNDEFINED: undefined? ROWSTATUS_ACTIVE: active? ROWSTATUS_NOTINSERVICE: notInService? ROWSTATUS_NOTREADY: notReady? ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW: createAndGo? ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDWAIT: createAndWait? ROWSTATUS_DESTROY: destroy.

hwAirScanVoiceAware.name: hwAirScanVoiceAware
hwAirScanVoiceAware.description: This object indicates the voice aware set. The default value is enable.

hwAirScanVideoAware.name: hwAirScanVideoAware
hwAirScanVideoAware.description: This object indicates the video aware set. The default value is enable.

hwAirScanSwitch.name: hwAirScanSwitch
hwAirScanSwitch.description: This object indicates the scan switch status. The default value is enable.

hwVapProfileTable.name: hwVapProfileTable
hwVapProfileTable.description: This table is used to configure and query VAP profile parameters.

hwVapProfileEntry.name: hwVapProfileEntry
hwVapProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwVapProfileName.

hwVapProfileName.name: hwVapProfileName
hwVapProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of a VAP profile. It is the index of the table.

hwVapForwardMode.name: hwVapForwardMode
hwVapForwardMode.description: This object indicates the service forwarding mode. The default value is 1.

hwVapTunnelForwardProtocol.name: hwVapTunnelForwardProtocol
hwVapTunnelForwardProtocol.description: This object indicates the format of packets forwarded by tunnel. The default value is 0xF.? bit0: dot1x? bit1: http? bit2: wapi? bit3: mdns.

hwVapServiceSwitch.name: hwVapServiceSwitch
hwVapServiceSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the VAP service function. The default value is 2.

hwVapAutoOffStartTime.name: hwVapAutoOffStartTime
hwVapAutoOffStartTime.description: This object indicates the start time of VAP profile. The format is HH:MM:SS.

hwVapAutoOffEndTime.name: hwVapAutoOffEndTime
hwVapAutoOffEndTime.description: This object indicates the end time of VAP profile. The format is HH:MM:SS.

hwVapTemporaryManagementSwitch.name: hwVapTemporaryManagementSwitch
hwVapTemporaryManagementSwitch.description: If this parameter is set to 2, the VAP automatically becomes the management VAP for offline APs after the AP is disconnected. It can still send signals so that maintenance personnel can access it to identify faults (the security mode is the non-authentication security mode and the SSID will be hidden). The default value is 1.

hwVapServiceVlan.name: hwVapServiceVlan
hwVapServiceVlan.description: This object indicates the service VLAN for the VAP. The default value is 1.

hwVapVlanPool.name: hwVapVlanPool
hwVapVlanPool.description: This object indicates the VLAN pool to which the VAP is bound.

hwVapType.name: hwVapType
hwVapType.description: This object indicates the VAP type. The default value is 1.

hwVapStaAccessMode.name: hwVapStaAccessMode
hwVapStaAccessMode.description: This object indicates the access mode. The default value is 1.

hwVapStaAccessModePorfile.name: hwVapStaAccessModePorfile
hwVapStaAccessModePorfile.description: This object indicates blacklist and whitelist profiles.

hwVapRoamHomeAgent.name: hwVapRoamHomeAgent
hwVapRoamHomeAgent.description: This object indicates the tunnel endpoint for inter-Layer 3 roaming. The default value is 1..

hwVapRoamVlanMobilityGroup.name: hwVapRoamVlanMobilityGroup
hwVapRoamVlanMobilityGroup.description: This object indicates the VLAN group for roaming. For the same VLAN, if the VAP is in different VLAN groups for roaming, the roaming is also inter-Layer 3 roaming. The default value is 1..

hwVapRoamLayer3Switch.name: hwVapRoamLayer3Switch
hwVapRoamLayer3Switch.description: This object indicates the status of the Layer 3 roaming function. The default value is 2.

hwVapBandSteerSwitch.name: hwVapBandSteerSwitch
hwVapBandSteerSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the band steering function. The default value is 2.

hwVapLearnIpv4Address.name: hwVapLearnIpv4Address
hwVapLearnIpv4Address.description: This object indicates the status of the IPv4 address learning function. The default value is 2.

hwVapLearnIpv6Address.name: hwVapLearnIpv6Address
hwVapLearnIpv6Address.description: This object indicates the status of the IPv6 address learning function. The default value is 2.

hwVapLearnIpv4AddressStrict.name: hwVapLearnIpv4AddressStrict
hwVapLearnIpv4AddressStrict.description: This object indicates the status of the strict address learning (only through the DHCP) function. The default value is 1.

hwVapIpBindCheck.name: hwVapIpBindCheck
hwVapIpBindCheck.description: This object indicates the status of the IP binding relationship check function. The default value is 1.

hwVapArpBindCheck.name: hwVapArpBindCheck
hwVapArpBindCheck.description: This object indicates the status of the ARP binding relationship check function. The default value is 1.

hwVapOptinon82InsertSwitch.name: hwVapOptinon82InsertSwitch
hwVapOptinon82InsertSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the function of appending the Option 82 field to DHCP messages. The default value is 1.

hwVapOptinon82InsertRidFormat.name: hwVapOptinon82InsertRidFormat
hwVapOptinon82InsertRidFormat.description: This object indicates the mode to append the Option 82 field to DHCP messages. The default value is 2.

hwVapDhcpTrustPort.name: hwVapDhcpTrustPort
hwVapDhcpTrustPort.description: This object indicates the status of the radio interface DHCP trust function. The default value is 1.

hwVapNdTrustPort.name: hwVapNdTrustPort
hwVapNdTrustPort.description: This object indicates the status of the radio interface ND trust function. The default value is 1.

hwVapSecurityProfile.name: hwVapSecurityProfile
hwVapSecurityProfile.description: The object indicates the security profile that is bound to the VAP. The default value is default.

hwVapTrafficProfile.name: hwVapTrafficProfile
hwVapTrafficProfile.description: The object indicates the traffic profile that is bound to the VAP. The default value is default.

hwVapSsidProfile.name: hwVapSsidProfile
hwVapSsidProfile.description: The object indicates the SSID profile that is bound to the VAP. The default value is default.

hwVapAuthenticationProfile.name: hwVapAuthenticationProfile
hwVapAuthenticationProfile.description: The object indicates the authentication profile that is bound to the VAP. The default value is default.

hwVapSacProfile.name: hwVapSacProfile
hwVapSacProfile.description: The object indicates the SAC profile that is bound to the VAP.

hwVapProfileRowStatus.name: hwVapProfileRowStatus
hwVapProfileRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.? ROWSTATUS_UNDEFINED: undefined? ROWSTATUS_ACTIVE: active? ROWSTATUS_NOTINSERVICE: notInService? ROWSTATUS_NOTREADY: notReady? ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW: createAndGo? ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDWAIT: createAndWait? ROWSTATUS_DESTROY: destroy.

hwVapUserProfile.name: hwVapUserProfile
hwVapUserProfile.description: The object indicates the user profile that is bound to the VAP.

hwVapHotspot2Profile.name: hwVapHotspot2Profile
hwVapHotspot2Profile.description: The object indicates the Hotspot2.0 profile that is bound to the VAP.

hwSoftgreProfile.name: hwSoftgreProfile
hwSoftgreProfile.description: The object indicates the Softgre profile that is bound to the VAP.

hwVapUccProfile.name: hwVapUccProfile
hwVapUccProfile.description: The object indicates the UCC profile that is bound to the VAP.

hwVapAntiAttackBroadcastFloodSwitch.name: hwVapAntiAttackBroadcastFloodSwitch
hwVapAntiAttackBroadcastFloodSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the VAP anti-attack braoadcast flood function. The default value is 2.

hwVapAntiAttackBroadcastFloodStaRateThre.name: hwVapAntiAttackBroadcastFloodStaRateThreshold
hwVapAntiAttackBroadcastFloodStaRateThre.description: This object indicates the anti-attack braoadcast flood sta-rate-threshold for the VAP. The default value is 10.

hwVapAntiAttackBroadcastFloodBlacklistSw.name: hwVapAntiAttackBroadcastFloodBlacklistSwitch
hwVapAntiAttackBroadcastFloodBlacklistSw.description: This object indicates the status of the VAP anti-attack braoadcast flood blacklist function. The default value is 1.

hwVapLearnIpv6AddressStrict.name: hwVapLearnIpv6AddressStrict
hwVapLearnIpv6AddressStrict.description: This object indicates the status of the strict address learning (only through the DHCPv6) function. The default value is 1.

hwVapAntiAttackARPFloodSwitch.name: hwVapAntiAttackARPFloodSwitch
hwVapAntiAttackARPFloodSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the VAP anti-attack ARP flood function. The default value is 2.

hwVapAntiAttackARPFloodStaRateThreshold.name: hwVapAntiAttackARPFloodStaRateThreshold
hwVapAntiAttackARPFloodStaRateThreshold.description: This object indicates the anti-attack ARP flood sta-rate-threshold for the VAP. The default value is 5.

hwVapAntiAttackARPFloodBlacklistSwitch.name: hwVapAntiAttackARPFloodBlacklistSwitch
hwVapAntiAttackARPFloodBlacklistSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the VAP anti-attack ARP flood blacklist function. The default value is 1.

hwVapAntiAttackNDFloodSwitch.name: hwVapAntiAttackNDFloodSwitch
hwVapAntiAttackNDFloodSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the VAP anti-attack ND flood function. The default value is 2.

hwVapAntiAttackNDFloodStaRateThreshold.name: hwVapAntiAttackNDFloodStaRateThreshold
hwVapAntiAttackNDFloodStaRateThreshold.description: This object indicates the anti-attack ND flood sta-rate-threshold for the VAP. The default value is 16.

hwVapAntiAttackNDFloodBlacklistSwitch.name: hwVapAntiAttackNDFloodBlacklistSwitch
hwVapAntiAttackNDFloodBlacklistSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the VAP anti-attack ND flood blacklist function. The default value is 1.

hwVapAntiAttackIGMPFloodSwitch.name: hwVapAntiAttackIGMPFloodSwitch
hwVapAntiAttackIGMPFloodSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the VAP anti-attack IGMP flood function. The default value is 2.

hwVapAntiAttackIGMPFloodStaRateThreshold.name: hwVapAntiAttackIGMPFloodStaRateThreshold
hwVapAntiAttackIGMPFloodStaRateThreshold.description: This object indicates the anti-attack IGMP flood sta-rate-threshold for the VAP. The default value is 4.

hwVapAntiAttackIGMPFloodBlacklistSwitch.name: hwVapAntiAttackIGMPFloodBlacklistSwitch
hwVapAntiAttackIGMPFloodBlacklistSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of the VAP anti-attack IGMP flood blacklist function. The default value is 1.

hwVapDefenceProfile.name: hwVapDefenceProfile
hwVapDefenceProfile.description: The object indicates the Defence profile that is bound to the VAP.

hwVapPermitVlanList.name: hwVapPermitVlanList
hwVapPermitVlanList.description: This object indicates the PermitVlanList. The default value is 0.

hwSsidProfileTable.name: hwSsidProfileTable
hwSsidProfileTable.description: This table is used to configure and query SSID profile parameters.

hwSsidProfileEntry.name: hwSsidProfileEntry
hwSsidProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwSsidProfileName.

hwSsidProfileName.name: hwSsidProfileName
hwSsidProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of a VAP profile. It is the index of the table.

hwSsidText.name: hwSsidText
hwSsidText.description: This object indicates the SSID character string. The default value is huawei-default.

hwSsidHide.name: hwSsidHide
hwSsidHide.description: This object indicates whether to enable SSID hiding. The default value is 1.

hwSsidAssocTimeout.name: hwSsidAssocTimeout
hwSsidAssocTimeout.description: This object indicates the association timeout period of a user. The default value is 5 minutes.

hwSsidMaxStaNum.name: hwSsidMaxStaNum
hwSsidMaxStaNum.description: The object indicates the number of access users on a VAP. The default value is 64.

hwSsidLegacyStaSwitch.name: hwSsidLegacyStaSwitch
hwSsidLegacyStaSwitch.description: This object indicates whether to allow access from legacy terminals. The default value is 2.

hwSsidDtimInterval.name: hwSsidDtimInterval
hwSsidDtimInterval.description: This object indicates the DTIM interval. The default value is 3.

hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceECWmax.name: hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceECWmax
hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceECWmax.description: This object indicates the ECWmax value, which determines the average avoidance time. The value of this object is the ECWmax value of the AC_VO queue on the station. The default value is 3.

hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceECWmin.name: hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceECWmin
hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceECWmin.description: This object indicates the ECWmin value, which determines the average avoidance time. The value of this object is the ECWmin value of the AC_VO queue on the station. The default value is 2.

hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceAIFSN.name: hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceAIFSN
hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceAIFSN.description: This object indicates the AIFSN value, which determines the idle waiting time. The value of this object is the AIFSN value of the AC_VO queue on the station. The default value is 2.

hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceTXOPLimit.name: hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceTXOPLimit
hwSsidClientEdcaVoiceTXOPLimit.description: This object indicates the TXOPLimit value, which determines the time for occupying the channel. The value of this object is the TXOPLimit value of the AC_VO queue on the station. The default value is 47.

hwSsidClientEdcaVideoECWmax.name: hwSsidClientEdcaVideoECWmax
hwSsidClientEdcaVideoECWmax.description: This object indicates the ECWmax value, which determines the average avoidance time. The value of this object is the ECWmax value of the AC_VI queue on the station. The default value is 4.

hwSsidClientEdcaVideoECWmin.name: hwSsidClientEdcaVideoECWmin
hwSsidClientEdcaVideoECWmin.description: This object indicates the ECWmin value, which determines the average avoidance time. The value of this object is the ECWmin value of the AC_VI queue on the station. The default value is 3.

hwSsidClientEdcaBeAIFSN.name: hwSsidClientEdcaBeAIFSN

hwSsidClientEdcaBkAIFSN.name: hwSsidClientEdcaBkAIFSN

hwSsidClientEdcaBkTXOPLimit.name: hwSsidClientEdcaBkTXOPLimit

hwSsidInboundCarCbs.name: hwSsidInboundCarCbs
hwSsidInboundCarCbs.description: This object indicates the inbound committed burst size (CBS) of the SSID. The default value is 0 bytes. Invalid value is 1 to 1499.

hwSsidInboundCarPbs.name: hwSsidInboundCarPbs

hwSsidOutboundCarCir.name: hwSsidOutboundCarCir

hwSsidOutboundCarPir.name: hwSsidOutboundCarPir
hwSsidOutboundCarPir.description: This object indicates the outbound peak information rate (PIR) of the SSID. The default value is 0 kbit/s. Invalid value is 1 to 63.

hwSsidOutboundCarCbs.name: hwSsidOutboundCarCbs
hwSsidOutboundCarCbs.description: This object indicates the outbound committed burst size (CBS) of the SSID. The default value is 0 bytes. Invalid value is 1 to 1499.

hwSsidOutboundCarPbs.name: hwSsidOutboundCarPbs
hwSsidOutboundCarPbs.description: This object indicates the outbound peak burst size (PBS) of the SSID. The default value is 0 bytes. Invalid value is 1 to 1499.

hwSecurityProfileName.name: hwSecurityProfileName
hwSecurityProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of a security profile. It is the index of the table.

hwSecurityPolicy.name: hwSecurityPolicy
hwSecurityPolicy.description: This object indicates the air interface authentication policy. The default value is 8(open).

hwSecurityWepEncrypt.name: hwSecurityWepEncrypt
hwSecurityWepEncrypt.description: This object indicates the WEP encryption algorithm. The default value is 4369.

hwSecurityWepPskMode.name: hwSecurityWepPskMode
hwSecurityWepPskMode.description: This object indicates that the WEP PSK mode is PassPhase or Hex. The default value is 4369.

hwSecurityWepPsk1.name: hwSecurityWepPsk1
hwSecurityWepPsk1.description: This object indicates the WEP PSK1.

hwSecurityWepPsk2.name: hwSecurityWepPsk2
hwSecurityWepPsk2.description: This object indicates the WEP PSK2.

hwSecurityWepPsk3.name: hwSecurityWepPsk3
hwSecurityWepPsk3.description: This object indicates the WEP PSK3.

hwSecurityWepPsk4.name: hwSecurityWepPsk4
hwSecurityWepPsk4.description: This object indicates the WEP PSK4.

hwSecurityWepDefaultKeyId.name: hwSecurityWepDefaultKeyId
hwSecurityWepDefaultKeyId.description: This object indicates the default key ID for WEP. The default value is 1.

hwSecurityWpaEncrypt.name: hwSecurityWpaEncrypt
hwSecurityWpaEncrypt.description: This object indicates the WPA/WPA2 encryption algorithm.

hwSecurityWpaPskMode.name: hwSecurityWpaPskMode
hwSecurityWpaPskMode.description: This object indicates whether the WPA PSK mode is PassPhase or Hex.

hwSecurityWpaPsk.name: hwSecurityWpaPsk
hwSecurityWpaPsk.description: This object indicates the WPA/WPA2 PSK.

hwSecurityWpaPtkUpdateSwitch.name: hwSecurityWpaPtkUpdateSwitch
hwSecurityWpaPtkUpdateSwitch.description: This object indicates the status of WPA PTK update function. The default value is 1.

hwSecurityWpaPtkUpdateInterval.name: hwSecurityWpaPtkUpdateInterval

hwSecurityWapiPskMode.name: hwSecurityWapiPskMode

hwSecurityWapiPsk.name: hwSecurityWapiPsk
hwSecurityWapiPsk.description: This object indicates the WAPI PSK.

hwSecurityWapiAsuIpAddress.name: hwSecurityWapiAsuIpAddress
hwSecurityWapiAsuIpAddress.description: This object indicates the IP address of the WAPI ASU.

hwSecurityWapiIssuerCertFileName.name: hwSecurityWapiIssuerCertFileName
hwSecurityWapiIssuerCertFileName.description: This object indicates the certificate file name of the WAPI issuer.

hwSecurityWapiAsuCertFileName.name: hwSecurityWapiAsuCertFileName
hwSecurityWapiAsuCertFileName.description: This object indicate the certificate file name of the WAPI ASU.

hwSecurityWapiAcCertFileName.name: hwSecurityWapiAcCertFileName
hwSecurityWapiAcCertFileName.description: This object indicate the certificate file name of the WAPI AC.

hwSecurityWapiAcPrvKeyFileName.name: hwSecurityWapiAcPrvKeyFileName
hwSecurityWapiAcPrvKeyFileName.description: This object indicates the private key file name of the WAPI AC.

hwSecurityWapiIssuerPfxPassword.name: hwSecurityWapiIssuerPfxPassword
hwSecurityWapiIssuerPfxPassword.description: This object indicates the WAPI issuer certificate key.

hwSecurityWapiAsuPfxPassword.name: hwSecurityWapiAsuPfxPassword
hwSecurityWapiAsuPfxPassword.description: This object indicates the WAPI ASU certificate key.

hwSecurityWapiAcPfxPassword.name: hwSecurityWapiAcPfxPassword
hwSecurityWapiAcPfxPassword.description: This object indicates the WAPI AC certificate key.

hwSecurityWapiAcPrvKeyPassword.name: hwSecurityWapiAcPrvKeyPassword
hwSecurityWapiAcPrvKeyPassword.description: This object indicates the key for reading the AC private key file.

hwSecurityWapiCertRetransCount.name: hwSecurityWapiCertRetransCount
hwSecurityWapiCertRetransCount.description: This object indicates the number of retransmissions of WAPI certificate authentication packets. The default value is 3.

hwSecurityWapiBkThreshold.name: hwSecurityWapiBkThreshold
hwSecurityWapiBkThreshold.description: This object indicates the WAPI BK lifetime percentage. The default value is 70.

hwSecurityWapiBkLifetime.name: hwSecurityWapiBkLifetime
hwSecurityWapiBkLifetime.description: This object indicates the interval for updating the WAPI BK. The default value is 43200 seconds.

hwSecurityWapiUskUpdateMethod.name: hwSecurityWapiUskUpdateMethod
hwSecurityWapiUskUpdateMethod.description: This object indicates the WAPI USK update mode. The default value is 2.

hwSecurityWapiMskUpdateMethod.name: hwSecurityWapiMskUpdateMethod
hwSecurityWapiMskUpdateMethod.description: This object indicates the WAPI MSK update mode. The default value is 2.

hwSecurityWapiUskUpdateInterval.name: hwSecurityWapiUskUpdateInterval
hwSecurityWapiUskUpdateInterval.description: This object indicates the time-based interval for updating the WAPI USK. The default value is 86400 seconds.

hwSecurityWapiUskUpdatePackets.name: hwSecurityWapiUskUpdatePackets
hwSecurityWapiUskUpdatePackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets that will trigger WAPI USK update. The default value is 10.

hwSecurityWapiUskRetansCount.name: hwSecurityWapiUskRetansCount
hwSecurityWapiUskRetansCount.description: This object indicates the maximum number of retransmissions of a WAPI USK negotiation packet. The default value is 3.

hwSecurityWapiMskUpdateInterval.name: hwSecurityWapiMskUpdateInterval
hwSecurityWapiMskUpdateInterval.description: This object indicates the time-based interval for updating the WAPI MSK. The default value is 86400 seconds.

hwSecurityWapiMskUpdatePackets.name: hwSecurityWapiMskUpdatePackets
hwSecurityWapiMskUpdatePackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets that will trigger WAPI MSK update. The default value is 10.

hwSecurityWapiMskRetansCount.name: hwSecurityWapiMskRetansCount
hwSecurityWapiMskRetansCount.description: This object indicates the maximum number of retransmissions of a WAPI MSK negotiation packet. The default value is 3.

hwSecurityWapiSATimeout.name: hwSecurityWapiSATimeout
hwSecurityWapiSATimeout.description: This object indicates the timeout period of a WAPI-based security association (SA). The default value is 60 seconds.

hwSecurityPMF.name: hwSecurityPMF
hwSecurityPMF.description: This object indicates the status of the PMF function. The default value is 1.

hwSecurityProfileRowStatus.name: hwSecurityProfileRowStatus
hwSecurityProfileRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwAPTrafficProfileTable.name: hwAPTrafficProfileTable
hwAPTrafficProfileTable.description: This table is used to configure and query traffic profile parameters.

hwAPTrafficProfileEntry.name: hwAPTrafficProfileEntry
hwAPTrafficProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwAPTrafficProfileName.

hwAPTrafficProfileName.name: hwAPTrafficProfileName
hwAPTrafficProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of a traffic profile.

hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityMapDnTrustMode.name: hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityMapDnTrustMode
hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityMapDnTrustMode.description: This object indicates the downstream service priority mapping mode. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityDscpDnMap80211.name: hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityDscpDnMap80211e
hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityDscpDnMap80211.description: This object indicates the mapping relationship between 802.1p priorities of 802.3 packets and user priorities of 802.11 packets when data packets are sent to a downstream AP. DSCP values range from 0 to 63 and 802.11e priorities range from 0 to 7. Two mapped data are separated by a comma.

hwAPTrafficProfilePriority80211eUpMapDsc.name: hwAPTrafficProfilePriority80211eUpMapDscp
hwAPTrafficProfilePriority80211eUpMapDsc.description: This object indicates the tunnel priority mappings when data packets are sent from APs to an AC. DSCP values range from 0 to 63 and 802.11e priorities range from 0 to 7. Two mapped data are separated by a comma.

hwAPTrafficProfileUserIsolate.name: hwAPTrafficProfileUserIsolate
hwAPTrafficProfileUserIsolate.description: This object indicates the user isolation mode. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitClientUp.name: hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitClientUp
hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitClientUp.description: This object indicates the STA's uplink rate limit. The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF. It is expressed in kbit/s.

hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitClientDn.name: hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitClientDn
hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitClientDn.description: This object indicates the STA's downlink rate limit. The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF. It is expressed in kbit/s.

hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitVapUp.name: hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitVapUp
hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitVapUp.description: This object indicates the VAP's uplink rate limit. The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF. It is expressed in kbit/s.

hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitVapDn.name: hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitVapDn
hwAPTrafficProfileRateLimitVapDn.description: This object indicates the VAP's downlink rate limit. The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF. It is expressed in kbit/s.

hwAPTrafficProfileMldSnooping.name: hwAPTrafficProfileMldSnooping
hwAPTrafficProfileMldSnooping.description: This object indicates the status of the MLD snooping function. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnooping.name: hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnooping
hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnooping.description: This object indicates the status of the IGMP snooping function. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnoopingReportSupp.name: hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnoopingReportSuppress
hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnoopingReportSupp.description: This object indicates the status of the IGMP snooping report suppression function. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfileMcToUc.name: hwAPTrafficProfileMcToUc
hwAPTrafficProfileMcToUc.description: This object indicates the status of the function of converting multicast to unicast. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeSuppressionBc.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeSuppressionBc
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeSuppressionBc.description: This object indicates the information about broadcast storm suppression. The unit is pps. The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF, indicating that the broadcast storm suppression is not enabled.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeSuppressionUc.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeSuppressionUc
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeSuppressionUc.description: This object indicates the information about unknown unicast storm suppression. The unit is pps. The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF, indicating that the broadcast storm suppression is not enabled.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeSuppressionMc.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeSuppressionMc
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeSuppressionMc.description: This object indicates the information about multicast storm suppression. The unit is pps. The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF, indicating that the broadcast storm suppression is not enabled.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeTCPAdjustMSS.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeTCPAdjustMSS
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeTCPAdjustMSS.description: This object indicates the information about the automatic MSS adjustment. The default value is 0xFFFFFFFF, indicating that this function is not enabled.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeProxyARP.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeProxyARP
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeProxyARP.description: This object indicates the status of the ARP proxy function. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeProxyND.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeProxyND
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeProxyND.description: This object indicates the status of the ND proxy function. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeUcSendARP.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeUcSendARP
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeUcSendARP.description: This object indicates the status of the unicast ARP function. The default value is 2.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeUcSendND.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeUcSendND
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeUcSendND.description: This object indicates the status of the unicast ND function. The default value is 2.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeUcSendDHCP.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeUcSendDHCP
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeUcSendDHCP.description: This object indicates the status of the unicast DHCP function. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeBcMcDenyAll.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeBcMcDenyAll
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeBcMcDenyAll.description: After this function is enabled, other multicast packets, except for proxy response packets and multicast packets converted to unicast packets, are discarded. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeStaBridgeForwa.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeStaBridgeForward
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeStaBridgeForwa.description: This object indicates the status of the STA bridge forwarding function. The default value is 2.

hwAPTrafficProfileRowStatus.name: hwAPTrafficProfileRowStatus
hwAPTrafficProfileRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityMapUpTrustMode.name: hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityMapUpTrustMode
hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityMapUpTrustMode.description: This object indicates the tunnel priority mapping mode.

hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityDscpUpMapDscp.name: hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityDscpUpMapDscp
hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityDscpUpMapDscp.description: This object indicates the mapping relationship between DSCP and DSCP. DSCP values range from 0 to 63. Two mapped data are separated by a comma.

hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeBcMcMismatchAc.name: hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeBcMcMismatchAct
hwAPTrafficProfileOptimizeBcMcMismatchAc.description: This object indicates the status of the bcmc unicast send mismacth action function. The default value is 1.

hwAPTrafficProfileMcToUcDynamicAdatptive.name: hwAPTrafficProfileMcToUcDynamicAdatptive
hwAPTrafficProfileMcToUcDynamicAdatptive.description: This object indicates the status of the multicast to unicast dynamic adaptive function. The default value is 2.

hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnoopingMaxBandwid.name: hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnoopingMaxBandwidth
hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnoopingMaxBandwid.description: This object indicates the status of the IGMP snooping max bandwidth function. The invalid value is 0.

hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnoopingMaxUser.name: hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnoopingMaxUser
hwAPTrafficProfileIGMPSnoopingMaxUser.description: This object indicates the status of the IGMP snooping max user function. The invalid value is 0.

hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityDscpUpMap8021p.name: hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityDscpUpMap8021p
hwAPTrafficProfilePriorityDscpUpMap8021p.description: This object indicates the mapping relationship between DSCP and 802.1p. DSCP values range from 0 to 63. Two mapped data are separated by a comma.

hwAPTrafficProfilePriority80211eUpMap802.name: hwAPTrafficProfilePriority80211eUpMap8021p
hwAPTrafficProfilePriority80211eUpMap802.description: This object indicates the mapping relationship between 802.11e and 802.1p. 802.11e values range from 0 to 7. Two mapped data are separated by a comma.

hwAPTrafficProfilePriority8021pDnMap8021.name: hwAPTrafficProfilePriority8021pDnMap80211e
hwAPTrafficProfilePriority8021pDnMap8021.description: This object indicates the mapping relationship between 802.11e and 802.1p. 802.11e values range from 0 to 7. Two mapped data are separated by a comma.
