hwAPTrafficProfileFilterTable.description: This table is used to configure QoS filter information.

hwAPTrafficProfileFilterDirection.description: This object indicates the ACL rule direction for packet filtering in a traffic profile. This parameter has no default value.

hwAPTrafficProfileFilterType.description: This object indicates the ACL rule type for packet filtering in a traffic profile. This parameter has no default value.

hwAPTrafficProfileFilterACLID.name: hwAPTrafficProfileFilterACLID
hwAPTrafficProfileFilterACLID.description: This object indicates the ACL rule for packet filtering in a traffic profile.

hwAPTrafficProfileFilterRowStatus.name: hwAPTrafficProfileFilterRowStatus
hwAPTrafficProfileFilterRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwWlanVlanPoolTable.description: This table is used to configure VLAN pools.

hwWlanVlanPoolEntry.description: The index of this table is hwVlanPoolName.

hwVlanPoolName.description: This object indicates the VLAN pool name. It is the index of the table.

hwVlanPoolVlanlist.name: hwVlanPoolVlanlist
hwVlanPoolVlanlist.description: This object indicates the VLAN list.

hwVlanPoolAssignMethod.name: hwVlanPoolAssignMethod
hwVlanPoolAssignMethod.description: This object indicates the VLAN pool allocation algorithm. The default value is 1.

hwVlanPoolRowStatus.name: hwVlanPoolRowStatus
hwVlanPoolRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileTable.name: hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileTable
hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileTable.description: This table is used to create STA whitelist profiles.

hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileEntry.name: hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileEntry
hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileName.

hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of a STA whitelist profile. It is the index of the table.

hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileRowStatus.name: hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileRowStatus
hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table.

hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileConfigTable.name: hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileConfigTable
hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileConfigTable.description: This table is used to configure STA whitelist profiles.

hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileConfigEntry.name: hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileConfigEntry
hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileConfigEntry.description: The indexes of this table are hwWlanStaWhitelistProfileName and hwWlanStaWhitelistStaMac.

hwWlanStaWhitelistRowStatus.name: hwWlanStaWhitelistRowStatus
hwWlanStaWhitelistRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwWlanStaWhitelistStaMacDescription.name: hwWlanStaWhitelistStaMacDescription
hwWlanStaWhitelistStaMacDescription.description: This object indicates the description of the sta-mac.

hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileTable.name: hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileTable
hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileTable.description: This table is used to create STA blacklist profiles.

hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileEntry.name: hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileEntry
hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileName.

hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileName.description: This object indicates the STA blacklist profile name. It is the index of the table.

hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileRowStatus.name: hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileRowStatus
hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileConfigTable.name: hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileConfigTable
hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileConfigTable.description: This table is used to configure STA blacklist profiles.

hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileConfigEntry.name: hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileConfigEntry
hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileConfigEntry.description: The indexes of this table are hwWlanStaBlacklistProfileName and hwWlanStaBlacklistStaMac.

hwWlanStaBlacklistRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwWlanStaBlacklistStaMacDescription.name: hwWlanStaBlacklistStaMacDescription
hwWlanStaBlacklistStaMacDescription.description: This object indicates the description of the sta-mac.

hwWidsProfileTable.name: hwWidsProfileTable
hwWidsProfileTable.description: This table is used to configure WIDS classify profiles, WIDS attack profiles, and WIDS contain profiles.

hwWidsProfileEntry.name: hwWidsProfileEntry
hwWidsProfileEntry.description: The index of this table is hwWidsProfileName.

hwWidsProfileName.name: hwWidsProfileName
hwWidsProfileName.description: This object indicates the name of a WIDS profile. It is the index of the table.

hwWidsProfileRowStatus.name: hwWidsProfileRowStatus
hwWidsProfileRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status of this table. ROWSTATUS_CREATEANDFLOW and ROWSTATUS_DESTROY are commonly used.

hwWidsDeviceReportInterval.name: hwWidsDeviceReportInterval
hwWidsDeviceReportInterval.description: This object indicates the device detection reporting interval. The default value is 300 seconds.

hwWidsDeviceSyncInterval.name: hwWidsDeviceSyncInterval
hwWidsDeviceSyncInterval.description: This object indicates the interval for APs to report all device information to an AC. The default value is 360 minutes.

hwWidsSpoofProfile.name: hwWidsSpoofProfile
hwWidsSpoofProfile.description: This object indicates the name of a WIDS spoof profile.

hwWidsWhitelistProfile.name: hwWidsWhitelistProfile
hwWidsWhitelistProfile.description: This object indicates the name of a WIDS confident profile.

hwWidsBruteForceDetectInterval.name: hwWidsBruteForceDetectInterval
hwWidsBruteForceDetectInterval.description: This object indicates the interval for brute force attack detection. The default value is 60. It is expressed in s.

hwWidsBruteForceDetectThreshold.name: hwWidsBruteForceDetectThreshold
hwWidsBruteForceDetectThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for the number of brute force attack attempts, namely, the threshold for the number of key negotiation failures within a detection period. If the number of brute-force attack attempts exceeds the threshold, the terminal initiates brute force attacks. The default value is 20.

hwWidsBruteForceQuietTime.name: hwWidsBruteForceQuietTime
hwWidsBruteForceQuietTime.description: This object indicates the quiet period for brute force attack alarm reporting. The default value is 600 seconds.

hwWidsFloodDetectInterval.name: hwWidsFloodDetectInterval
hwWidsFloodDetectInterval.description: This object indicates the flood attack detection interval. The default value is 60. It is expressed in s.

hwWidsFloodDetectThreshold.name: hwWidsFloodDetectThreshold
